    <h3 id="p1"><span class="sec-num">01</span> Information We Collect</h3>
    <p><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email, phone number, organisation name, yard type, and registration number collected at signup.</p>
    <p><strong>Operational Data:</strong> Vehicle intake records, weighbridge data, inventory entries, compliance documents, and all data you enter while operating the Platform.</p>
    <p><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, pages visited, and session duration collected for security monitoring and service improvement.</p>
    <p><strong>Payment Data:</strong> Billing information processed via RBI-compliant gateways. Raw card numbers are never stored on our servers.</p>

    <h3 id="p2"><span class="sec-num">02</span> How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide, operate, and maintain the SMS Platform services</li>
      <li>To process transactions and send related billing communications</li>
      <li>To generate compliance reports under MoRTH Vehicle Scrappage Policy 2021</li>
      <li>To send service notifications, security alerts, and account messages</li>
      <li>To improve Platform features using anonymised usage analytics</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests and resolve disputes</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations under Indian law</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="p3"><span class="sec-num">03</span> Data Sharing &amp; Disclosure</h3>
    <p>We <strong>never sell, trade, or rent</strong> your personal information. We may share data with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> AWS India (hosting), email delivery, and payment processors under strict data processing agreements</li>
      <li><strong>Government Authorities:</strong> As required by MoRTH, VAHAN portal integration, or lawful government orders</li>
      <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In a merger or acquisition scenario with prior user notification</li>
      <li><strong>With Consent:</strong> Any other sharing only with your explicit permission</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="p4"><span class="sec-num">04</span> Data Storage &amp; Security</h3>
    <p>All data is stored on servers in India (AWS ap-south-1 Mumbai). Security measures include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>AES-256 encryption at rest and TLS 1.3 in transit</li>
      <li>Multi-factor authentication for all administrative access</li>
      <li>Annual third-party penetration testing</li>
      <li>Automated daily backups with 30-day retention</li>
      <li>SOC 2 Type II compliant infrastructure</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="p5"><span class="sec-num">05</span> Cookies &amp; Tracking</h3>
    <p>We use <strong>strictly necessary session cookies</strong> to maintain your login state. We do not use advertising cookies or third-party tracking pixels. Disabling cookies in your browser may affect Platform functionality.</p>

    <h3 id="p6"><span class="sec-num">06</span> Your Rights</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
      <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request account and data deletion (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
      <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Export operational data in CSV/Excel from the Platform at any time</li>
      <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing for specific purposes</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@sms-platform.in">privacy@sms-platform.in</a>.</p>

    <h3 id="p7"><span class="sec-num">07</span> Data Retention</h3>
    <p>Account data is retained for the duration of your subscription plus 90 days for recovery, then permanently deleted. Compliance documents may be retained longer as required by law.</p>

    <h3 id="p8"><span class="sec-num">08</span> Children's Privacy</h3>
    <p>The Platform is not directed at persons under 18. If we become aware a minor has provided data, we delete it promptly.</p>

    <h3 id="p9"><span class="sec-num">09</span> Changes to This Policy</h3>
    <p>Material changes are communicated via email at least 14 days before taking effect. Continued use indicates acceptance.</p>

